\section*{Chapter Three Part Three: Deciding which Numerical Summaries to Use}

\subsection*{Review}

Remember last class period we talked about different types of summary statistics:

\textbf{Measures of Center}
\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Mean:} ~\\\\\\
  \item \textbf{Median:} ~\\\\\\
\end{itemize}

\textbf{Measures of Spread}
\begin{itemize}
  \item \textbf{Range:} ~\\\\\\
  \item \textbf{IQR:} ~\\\\\\
  \item \textbf{Standard Deviation} ~\\\\\\
\end{itemize}

We call summary statistics NOT affected by outliers \underline{\hspace{8cm}}.
